Quickstrike:





Quickstrike drew his head closer to the doorway of exitway of the base. The 
battle sounded like it had ceased. He kept listening just to make sure. The 
Maximals could make a counterattack. Maybe they were at the ramp right now, 
ready to blow the hatch down, and he and Mantella were right there.

The ambient was a numb silence. Quickstrike was a little unsettled by it. He 
could hear his own spark pulse with the quietness.

He leaned away from the hatchway and stood up straight.

"Sounds like it's over," he announced to Mantella near-by. It was a good 
thing to him. He rather now fight at this time. But if he had to, he was 
ready. He always was. Even if was injured.
